verify-xdp.sh: kernel 6.6; loading lb_xdp.bin via lvh
HARNESS-CAPTURED-PENDING-CI-RERUN
This file is a placeholder baseline emitted by ROUND8-L4-10's
implementation pass on a sandbox without `bpf-linker` available to
re-build the BPF ELF, nor a privileged Docker+lvh runner to actually
load it against a 6.6 kernel. The first green CI run on kernel 6.6
MUST refresh this file via:

    scripts/verify-xdp.sh --kernel 6.6 --update-baseline
    git add audit/ebpf/verifier-logs/6.6.log.committed

Until then, the `verify-xdp.sh` diff gate will fail-loud (exit 1) on
every change, which is the desired audit-of-audit posture — the
script being committed without the baseline (as in EBPF-2-07's
no-op state at ffde98c) is the failure mode this finding closes.

Expected content of a refreshed baseline (post-CI):
  - one section per BPF program section in lb_xdp.bin
  - verifier output lines with addresses normalised to 0xADDR
  - 'processed N insns' / 'peak_states N' counters
  - bpftool prog run verdict + dst-MAC rewrite assertion bytes
